  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Qualifications for Overseers"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is a trustworthy saying: If anyone aspires to be an overseer, he desires a noble task."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "An overseer, then, must be above reproach, the husband of but one wife,",
          {
            "noteId": 618
          },
          "temperate, self-controlled, respectable, hospitable, able to teach,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "not dependent on wine, not violent but gentle, peaceable, and free of the love of money."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "An overseer must manage his own household well and keep his children under control, with complete dignity."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "For if someone does not know how to manage his own household, how can he care for the church of God?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "He must not be a recent convert, or he may become conceited and fall under the same condemnation as the devil."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Furthermore, he must have a good reputation with outsiders, so that he will not fall into disgrace and into the snare of the devil."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Qualifications for Deacons"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "Deacons likewise must be dignified, not double-tongued or given to much wine or greedy for money."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "They must hold to the mystery of the faith with a clear conscience."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Additionally, they must first be tested. Then, if they are above reproach, let them serve as deacons."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "In the same way, the women",
          {
            "noteId": 619
          },
          "must be dignified, not slanderers, but temperate and faithful in all things."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "A deacon must be the husband of but one wife, a good manager of his children and of his own household."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "For those who have served well as deacons acquire for themselves a high standing and great confidence in the faith that is in Christ Jesus."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Mystery of Godliness"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "Although I hope to come to you soon, I am writing you these things"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "in case I am delayed, so that you will know how each one must conduct himself in Godâ€™s household, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and foundation of the truth."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "By common confession, the mystery of godliness is great:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "He appeared",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 620
          },
          {
            "text": "in the flesh,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "was vindicated by the Spirit,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 621
          },
          {
            "text": "was seen by angels,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "was proclaimed among the nations,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "was believed in throughout the world,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "was taken up in glory.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
